      "writtenOn": "2020-12-11T03:03:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It took me lots of time to figure out the relationship between emutation, mutation, preMut. WDYT the following structure.\n\n1. optional: Rename ApplyFunc to FollowUpActionFn. IIUC, the responsibility of applyFunc is to interact with other CV components to reflect the project state change?\n2. Make stateMachine.updateConfig directly returns FollowUpActionFn and possibly newState in the future CL instead of mutation struct\n3. Replace emutation with following struct.\n```\ntype stateTransition struct {\n  trigger    []string   // ID of the event\n  transitTo  *state\n  apply      ApplyFunc\n}\n\nfunc (t *transition) apply(ctx context.Context, p *dsset.PopOp) error {\n  // ...\n}\n```\n4. preMut could be renamed to something like calculateStateTransition.",
